cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use nybbloris, please cite it as below."
title: "nybbloris: LoRA fine-tuning and runtime-LoRA serving for NVFP4 MoE on consumer Blackwell"
abstract: >-
  LoRA fine-tuning and runtime-LoRA serving for NVFP4 (4-bit) mixture-of-experts models on a
  single DGX Spark (GB10, 128 GB unified memory). Trains the adapter on the served 4-bit weights
  directly (no BF16 round-trip, no re-quant drift) and ships a binding contract that proves the
  adapter changed the forward pass at serve time rather than silently serving the un-adapted base.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Freitag
    given-names: Niklas
version: "1.9"
date-released: "2026-07-06"
license: Apache-2.0
url: "https://github.com/NvMayMay/nvfp4-lora-spark"
repository-code: "https://github.com/NvMayMay/nvfp4-lora-spark"
keywords:
